## Instructions
1. `information_freshness_score`: 0 (severely outdated) to 1 (fully current). Consider the topic's rate of change and the dates mentioned in the article.
2. `potentially_outdated_claims`: identify claims that may be outdated with the claim text, date_context (the date or time period referenced), and reason_suspect (why it might be outdated).
3. `temporal_coverage_gap`: describe any significant time period not covered by the article (e.g. "No coverage of events after 2019").

## Output Format
JSON only:
{
  "information_freshness_score": 0.0,
  "potentially_outdated_claims": [{"claim": "string", "date_context": "string|null", "reason_suspect": "string|null"}],
  "temporal_coverage_gap": "string|null"
}
